John Clarkson, 55, from Preston, Lancashire, wrapped the Easter delicacies in pastry before they were battered and deep-fried .
The 'Pie-egg-ra' dish contains one and a half Cadbury's Creme Eggs and a side of chips .
Mr Clarkson says the savoury-sweet mix is a hit with customers who dip chips into the Creme Egg Pie 'yolk' like toast soldiers .